        ". Material from the building was incorporated into a basilica constructed nearby during the 5th or 6th century. Athens. The Oxford Encyclopedia of Classical Art and Architecture. Ed. John B. Hattendorf. Oxford University Press, 2007.             Over the following centuries, the temple was systematically quarried to provide building materials and material for the houses and churches of medieval Athens. By the end of the ": null
